						<summary>

						<p>Pillar in the Rāmēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>This damaged inscription mentions the names of Chōḷāmbika and Mārāmbika and seems to record a gift. The date portion in a chronogram, refers to Śaka 1. 76, the word for second digit is missing.</p>						

